**Content approach:** Competitors (livingaftermidnite, glamnaildesigns, nailzinbloom, sosyncd, thenailtech.org, Byrdie, InStyle, Country & Town House) are split between personality-first roundups (personality description → design list) and pure photo galleries with minimal editorial. The personality-first posts over-explain Libra traits that readers already know. The gallery-only posts give no editorial direction. Neither truly solves the Libra reader's core problem: indecision — "which one is actually *mine*?"

**Visual patterns:** Competitors typically use 20–40 images, many repetitive. High-save Pinterest posts use 8–15 curated images with specific design labelling. Inspirational intent benefits from quality over quantity.

**Recommended image count:** 10–14 — high-quality, curated, editorially labelled. Pinterest performance for Libra nails rewards specificity (image + design name) over volume.

